# Matrix (Rust) Plugin NEWS

## Version 0.1.0 (2026-02-17)

### Stability & Safety Improvements
- **Radical Thread Isolation:** All C callbacks from Rust worker threads are now "zero-touch," deferring all libpurple and GTK work to the main thread via `g_idle_add`.
- **Icon Safety & Deployment:** Added missing protocol icon installation to system paths and implemented file existence checks before setting buddy icons to prevent GdkPixbuf and GObject assertion failures.
- **Atomic Character Sanitization:** Implemented rigorous UTF-8 validation and BMP-only character filtering for all metadata (names, topics, groups) and message history to prevent Pango/GTK layout and font-scaling crashes.
- **Race Condition Resolution:** Refactored joining logic to defer history fetching until conversations are fully established in libpurple, preventing recursive initialization segfaults.
- **Connection Guarding:** Added robust account connection checks to all asynchronous processing to prevent operations on inactive accounts.
- **Icon Safety:** Added file existence checks before setting buddy icons to prevent GdkPixbuf and GObject assertion failures.

### Feature Enhancements
- **Command Discoverability:** Registered all Matrix-specific slash commands (/join, /invite, /poll, /sticker, /shrug, /reply, /thread) in the C plugin for tab-completion and /help visibility.
- **Global Account Actions:** Implemented global "Join Room", "Invite User", and "Manual SSO Token" actions available directly from the Account menu.
- **Sticker Optimization:** Added an in-memory cache for sticker MXC URIs to eliminate redundant file uploads.
- **Dashboard Fix:** Corrected the "Invite user" action in the Room Dashboard to use the appropriate invitation dialog.

### User Experience
- **Startup Throttling:** Implemented a calibrated delay during initial room population to ensure UI responsiveness.
- **Success Feedback:** Added user-visible confirmation messages for background tasks like room joining and invitations.
- **Security Warning:** Added a prominent warning dialog during login if insecure TLS mode is enabled.
